cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with functional logic programming languages and their semantics, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of programming languages (cs.PL), logic in computer science (cs.LO), functional programming (cs.FL), software engineering (cs.SE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper proposes two novel compositional plural semantics for constructor systems and studies their basic properties, which are relevant to all of these sub-categories. Therefore, cs.PL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.SE, and cs.DS.
